shared_text:
PBSLEARNINGMEDIA.ORG
PreK-12 Resources for Emergency Closings | PBS LearningMedia

Holly Benton Ackerman shared a link to the group: Family Resource and Youth Services Coalition of Kentucky (FRYSCKY).
March 26 at 9:48 AM ·

Hello all! I wanted to pass along a few resources from KET - Kentucky Educational Television and PBS

KET has launched a new website called Learn-at-Home. This website is for educators and caregivers! The resources are on air and online. https://www.ket.org/learnathome/

There are two collections in PBS LearningMedia to assist with NTI days. The collections have resources for children in PreK-12 grade. These collections were curated by PBS stations across the nations, including KET. There are printables as well as online resources that integrate with Google Classroom and other online platforms.

English: https://ket.pbslearningmedia.org/collection/emergency-closings-collection/

Spanish: https://ket.pbslearningmedia.org/collection/recursos-de-prek-12-para-cierres-de-emergencia/

If educators need other NTI resources they can reach out to KET at NTI@ket.org

There are many other resources out there. We at KET are here to help in any way we can! Please feel reach out to us! We have programming from Early Childhood to Adult Ed.

SHARE this information with your school staff!

post_text: Thanks to everyone who donated to the Go Pantry food drive! It was a huge success!! We collected 492 cans!! We will announce winners Tuesday at school! A special thanks to Mrs. Jones and her 3rd grade class for counting and using their great math skills to make charts to help me sort them!

post_text: Attention WVES parents: Mark your calendars for next week when we will be collecting cans of Ravioli/Spaghetti O's for Go Pantry! This organization helps our families throughout the year. There will be grade level prize drawings where two students from each grade will be able to choose lunch with a staff member or a Rice Krispies treat party for their classroom. One school wide grand prize winner will win a $50.00 gift card to Kohl's. (courtesy of the WVES PTA) Donations will be accepted at AR night. (2/11/20) As always thanks for supporting our Bearcat families!
